OL,3,CCampaigners say new laws will help in
OL,4,Cfight against spiking
OL,6,FIn 1989 she caught someone trying to
OL,7,Fput a pill into her drink and has
OL,8,Fspent the last 20 years fighting for
OL,9,Fmore support for victims and more
OL,10,Fprosecutions of offenders.
OL,12,FDawn was in Westminster for the speech
OL,13,Fand said: "This news is going to make
OL,14,Fsuch a huge difference to the future
OL,15,Fsafeguarding of men and women across
OL,16,Four country on what is really like an
OL,17,Finvisible crime.
