OL,3,CCampaigners say new laws will help in
OL,4,Cfight against spiking
OL,6,F"We're going to be able to start
OL,7,Fmaking sure that we're going to be
OL,8,Fgaining convictions, because at the
OL,9,Fmoment, we've got less than a 2%
OL,10,Fconviction rate. And this is something
OL,11,Fthat urgently needs to be changed.
OL,13,F"Our campaigning will always continue
OL,14,Fbecause spiking is an invisible crime.
OL,15,FIt doesn't just happen through drinks
OL,16,Feither. It happens through vapes,
OL,17,Fthrough food, via injection. So we all
OL,18,Fneed to be really vigilant and start
OL,19,Fworking together."
